# Run `go fix` after code changes

After modifying any Go source file, run `go fix` over the affected packages
before considering the change complete.

```bash
go fix ./...
```

- Run it once after a batch of related edits, not after every single file save.
- Review and keep any rewrites `go fix` applies (they migrate code to newer APIs).
- If `go fix` changes files, re-run `go build ./...` / `go test ./...` to confirm everything still compiles and passes.
